Factory Pattern

Factory design pattern is used to create objects or Class in Java at RUNTIME and it provides loose coupling and high cohesion.
Some time our application will not know that what kind of object it has to create at run-time.
When you don't want user to know every subclass and how the object is created.
Factory pattern hides creation logic which makes it easy to change it later when you change how object gets created

Read more: http://javarevisited.blogspot.com/2011/12/factory-design-pattern-java-example.html#ixzz3yPQkBK1p


What problem does it solve.

